<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-27T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/10–144:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-27T19:00:00-04:00">October
                                    27, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3677. Since MEW has instructed British Minister in Bern to join you in
                            approaching Swiss Minister of Foreign Affairs along lines of <pb facs="0789" n="779" xml:id="pg_779"/> Department’s 8178, October 6,
                            6 p.m. to London, repeated to Bern as Department’s 3509 [<hi rend="italic">3433</hi>], and subsequent telegrams, the Department
                            wonders if <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi> has been made (London’s 8956,
                            October 19, 8 p.m. to Department<note n="31" xml:id="d722fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> which London repeated to Bern). If not please make
                                <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi> as soon as possible and cable
                            Department urgently the result of this action.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>